(179, 1, '2014-04-10 18:49:56', '2014-04-10 18:49:56', 'Vegetarian restaurants are FINALLY catching on around the world – London included!\r\nFor the last two and half years, while I was living in Rome and flying back and forth to\r\nLondon, one of the things I always looked forward to eating in London was vegetarian\r\nfood.In Rome, there is always a wide variety of amazing Italian food, but let’s face it…\r\nproper Italian food generally has some form of meat in it. The idea of eating vegetarian\r\nfood, is not the most popular concept in Italy.\r\n\r\nWhen I used to go to someone’s dinner party and have to let them know that I didn’t eat\r\nmeat, they would say, “no problem, I’ll get you some prosciutto!” and then hand me a\r\nbig plate of prosciutto. Of course, I would politely take the plate, even though I wouldn’t\r\neat any of it, but I always wonder why so many Italians consider cured ham suitable\r\nfor vegetarians…\r\n\r\nOf course, this is not the case in London. Imagine the best Italian food, and then imagine\r\nit…vegetarian…and you have “Amico Bio”.\r\n\r\nYou will not find cured ham in this vegetarian Italian restaurant!\r\n\r\n“Amico” in Italian means “friend”, yet in this case, it is actually the last name of the man\r\nwho opened this great little place in 2010, Pasquale Amico. And you really get the\r\nsensation to be at a friend’s house when you eat here. Not only is the atmosphere\r\nquaint and intimate, but they change the menu frequently based on what they find\r\nin the market…just like they do in Italy.\r\n\r\nI used to like to come and eat here to have vegetarian food, and now that I am living in\r\nLondon, I like to eat here to feel like I am in Italy again. Don’t get scared by the word\r\n“vegetarian”…the food is so fresh and good, that it satisfies your pallet leaving you\r\nyearning to come back again and try all of the other interesting dishes that you didn’t\r\ntry yet.\r\n\r\nSimilar to Italian restaurants, they start their menu with appetizers…one definitely worth\r\ntrying is their arancini:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5925.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-288" alt="img_5925" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5925-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Amico Bio, London’s Italian Vegetarian</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> Restaurant </em><em>serves AMAZING organic food that</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> may just turn you vegetarian. These are Arancini </em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>di riso con mozzarella e piselli </em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em></em><em>(Rice croquettes filled with mozzarella and peas)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">They also have incredible salads:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_0006.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-287" alt="img_0006" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_0006-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Insalata di zucca grigliata</em>\r\n<em>(Roasted butternut squash salad)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_7097.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-286" alt="img_7097" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_7097-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Insalata di finocchio, arancia e rucola (fennel, orange and rocket salad)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">And of course, an interesting take on carpaccio…instead of meat or fish…they do vegetable capraccio!!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5950.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-285" alt="img_5950" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5950-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Carpaccio di zucca con scaglie di parmigiano (Pumpkin</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> carpaccio with shavings of parmigiano cheese)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_7098.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-284" alt="img_7098" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_7098-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Carpaccio di pera (Pear Carpaccio)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The main dishes are just as appetizing…</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_0008.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-294" alt="img_0008" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_0008-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Roasted butternut squash stuffed with quinoa on a bed of barley</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Risotto di Zucca (Pumpkin risotto)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_70991.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-293" alt="img_70991" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_70991-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Risotto di Zucca (Pumpkin risotto)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">And of course, being Italian, they also have amazing organic pizza:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5951.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-292" alt="img_5951" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5951-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Pizza con funghi, pomodorini e rucola</em>\r\n<em>(Pizza with mushrooms, rocket and cherry tomato)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5927.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-291" alt="img_5927" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5927-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Amico Bio: Pizza con zucca, mozzarella</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> di bufala, rosmarino e parmigiano</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>(Pizza with pumpkin, rosemary, buffalo </em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>mozzarella and parmigiano cheese)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5928.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-290" alt="img_5928" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5928-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>Amico Bio: Pizza con zucca, mozzarella </em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>di bufala, rosmarino e parmigiano</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>(Pizza with pumpkin, rosemary, buffalo</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em> mozzarella and parmigiano cheese)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">A word to the wise is to save a little room for dessert..made fresh everyday, I was lucky enough to try the Vegan apple crumble…better than most apple crumbles I have ever eaten!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5952.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-289" alt="img_5952" src="http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_5952-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>', 'RESTAURANT REVIEW: AMICO BIO, LONDON’S  PREMIER ITALIAN VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT', 'Vegetarian restaurants are FINALLY catching on around the world – London included!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'restaurant-review-amico-bio-londons-premier-italian-vegetarian-restaurant', '', '', '2014-04-17 21:25:13', '2014-04-17 21:25:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/london-food/?p=179', 0, 'post', '', 0),
