(265, 1, '2014-04-14 16:25:45', '2014-04-14 16:25:45', '<img alt="" src="http://localhost/london-food/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/intro1.jpg" width="" />\r\n\r\nI’ve only been here for less than a week, yet the vibe in this city is pretty clear:\r\n\r\n“London is on the move”.In one week, I’ve seen sun, rain, wind, currently a\r\n\r\ntube strike, and yet nothing stops these people. Yesterday I had to get into\r\n\r\nthe city center and ended up walking most of the way since there was so\r\n\r\nmuch traffic. Initially I was a bit worried about getting lost, but it was a lot\r\n\r\neasier than I thought and it was lovely to see all of the people going about their\r\n\r\ndays, despite the rain and crowds. Pubs were filled, cafés were busy, and\r\n\r\nrestaurants were running as normal.\r\n\r\nIn Rome, I remember not wanting to leave the house if we had the slightest bit\r\n\r\nof rain… And people would panic when the roads were wet, getting into silly\r\n\r\naccidents and slowing traffic to a halt.\r\n\r\nIn London? You’ve got a strike? You’ve got an enormous traffic jam?\r\n\r\nWhat do you do!? Rain or no rain..you WALK!\r\n\r\nYou ‘ve got to give it to Londoners-nothing gets in their way\r\n\r\nWe will answer all of your questions by phone or email once we receive the\r\n\r\ncompleted Private Tour Request Form.', 'RAIN, WIND, TRANSPORTATION STRIKES… NOTHING STOPS LONDONERS FROM  ENJOYING THEMSELVES.', '\r\nI’ve only been here for less than a week, yet the vibe in this city is pretty clear:\r\n“London is on the move”.In one week, I’ve seen sun, rain, wind, currently a', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-14 16:25:45', '2014-04-14 16:25:45', '', 181, 'http://localhost/london-food-lovers/181-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
